, Killaloe is a small regional town near Algonquin Park.

There is little of note in the town itself, but those heading to the park or to other remote areas might consider stopping here for provisions.  The popular Canadian snack "Beavertails" has named one of its signature versions after this town, though there is no place to acquire them locally.
The major access to Killaloe is Highway 60
The town itself is compact.  Any journeys to outlying regions would require a car.
The town itself offers little of interest, rather it is its proximity to wilderness.
For those heading to camping or for cottage country the town is reasonably stocked with a grocery market as well as some other stores.
